            <td width="560" height="96%" valign="top" align="left" style="padding-left: 10">
            <div class="PageHeading">
              <!-- #BeginEditable "PageHeading" -->
                        Grant and Incentive Programs
              <!-- #EndEditable --></div>
            <!-- #BeginEditable "Content" -->
            
            <table width="750"><tr><td>
<div align="center">
<table cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="0" width="85%" border="0" class="text-med">
<tr>
<td vAlign="top">


<p>
The Emission Reduction Incentive Program Group is responsible for the development, implementation, and on-going administration of all District grant and incentive programs, including the Heavy-Duty Engine Incentive and REMOVE II Programs.  These incentive programs provide a positive impact on air quality and are highly successful due to the fact that participation is voluntary.  
</p>
<p>
The District has operated incentive programs since 1992.  Over the years the District has been willing to develop new programs such as the Clean Green Yard Machine Program that helped consumers purchase electric lawnmowers.  This program will likely be continued in coming years if funding is available.
</p>


<ul>
	<li><a href="#applicantResources">Applicant Resources and Support Materials</a></li>
	<li><a href="#AgTractor">Agricultural Tractor / Mobile Equipment Replacement Program</a><font color="#FF0000"> 
	</font><font COLOR="#008000">(Heavy Duty Off-Road)</font></li>
	<!--  -->	
	<li><a href="#On-Road Voucher Incentive Program">On-Road Truck Voucher Programs</a>
	<font COLOR="#008000">(Heavy Duty Truck Replacement & Retrofit)</font><li><a href="#Proposition1B">Proposition 1B: Goods Movement Emission Reduction Program</a><font color="#FF0000"> 
	</font><font COLOR="#008000">(On-Road Heavy Duty Truck Replacement, Repower, and 
	Retrofit)</font></li>
	<li>

 

<a href="#WoodStoveChangeOut">Burn Cleaner Program</a> <font COLOR="#008000">
(Wood Stove Change Out)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#CleanGreenYardMachine">Clean Green Yard Machines Rebate Program</a>&nbsp;
	<font COLOR="#008000">(Lawn Mower Replacement Rebate Program)</font></li>
	<li><a href="GreatBasinPrograms.htm">Great Basin Program</a>
	<font COLOR="#008000">(Forklifts, Stationary Agricultural Pumps, Off-Road 
	Equipment)</font><br></li>
	<li><a href="#CordlessLawnMachine">Cordless Zero-Emission Commercial Lawn & Garden Equipment Demonstration Program</a>
	<font COLOR="#008000">(Commercial Demonstration Program)</font><br></li>
	<li><a href="#HeavyDuty">Heavy Duty Engine Program</a> <font COLOR="#008000">
	(Forklifts, Ag Pumps, Off-Road Equipment)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#PublicBenefitGrantProgram">Public Benefit Grant Program</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(New vehicles, infrastructure, and transportation)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#DriveCleanRebateProgram">Drive Clean! Rebate Program</a><font COLOR="#008000"> (Passenger Vehicles, Neighborhood Electric Vehicles, Zero-Emission Motorcycles)</font></li>
	
	<li><a href="#RemoveIIVVIP">Vanpool Voucher Incentive Program (VVIP)</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(Commuter vanpools)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#RemoveIIE-Mobility">E-Mobility Program, REMOVE II</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(Teleconferencing systems, e-Government, telecommute centers, distance learning facilities, etc.)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#RemoveIIE-Bike">Bicycle Infrastructure Program, REMOVE II</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(Class I or Class II bicycle path construction)</font></li>
	
	<li><a href="#RemoveIIE-PublicTrans">Public Transportation and Commuter Subsidy Program, REMOVE II</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(Public Transportation Passes, Park-and-Ride Lots)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#RemoveIIE-AltTrans">Alternative Fuel Vehicle Mechanic Training Program, REMOVE II</a> <font COLOR="#008000">(Alternative Fuel Mechanics Training)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#SchoolBusProgram">School Bus Incentives Program</a><font COLOR="#008000"> (SJVAPCD only; School Bus Retrofit and School Bus Replacement)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#SSBRP">Statewide School Bus Retrofit Program</a><font COLOR="#008000"> (School Bus Retrofit)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#LESBP">Lower-Emission School Bus Programs</a><font COLOR="#008000"> (School Bus Replacement, and Retrofit)</font></li>
	<li><a href="#Locomotive">Locomotive Program</a> (Locomotive Repower, and Replacement)</li>
	</ul>
<p>
For program descriptions please see below.  Please sign up for our 
<a href="../lists/list.htm">incentive e-mail lists</a> for notifications of program changes and availabilities.
</p>
<a name="applicantResources"></a>
<h1 class="button-text-wht">Applicant Resources and Support Materials</h1>
</p>

<p>
This section contains links to engine manufacturers, distributors and local 
dealers familiar with the requirements of the various incentive programs. The 
information and contacts within these links can assist you in obtaining all of 
the necessary information required for the program. Additionally, this page 
contains links to the California Air Resources Board website where you can 
obtain a list of eligible engines, vehicles, associated Executive Orders and 
other technical information.</p>

<p>

Please note that the manufacturers, distributors and dealers represented on this page and the information provided by the entities listed on this page are not 

"approved", "endorsed", "guaranteed", or "warranted" 
 by the SJVAPCD nor do they represent an exhaustive list of available resources.</p>
 
