<a name="nrcs"></a>
<h1 class="button-text-wht">Ag. Equipment Replacement Co-funded with Natural Resources Conservation Services (NRCS)</h1>
<p>The San Joaquin Valley Air Pollution Control District (SJVAPCD) is partnering with the Natural Resources Conservation Services (NRCS) to reduce emissions from off-road mobile agricultural sources.  The SJVAPCD is now accepting applications for 
<b>equipment replacements</b> only, from applicants who have applied to the NRCS program.  With joint funding applicants can qualify for a maximum of up to 80% of the cost of the new equipment. Applicants need to Qualify for EQIP with your local Farm Service Agency (FSA) and Complete the NRCS application at the same time as applying to the SJVAPCD.  A complete separate application needs to be submitted per piece of equipment.  Applicants who wish to trade in multiple pieces of equipment towards the purchase of a single new piece of equipment may submit all equipment information on a single application.  The deadline to apply is 
<b>close of business day June 26, 2009</b>, postmarked applications will not be accepted.  It is encouraged that applicants personally deliver their applications to the SJVAPCD Fresno office and have a staff member review their application for completion at that time.  This will ensure that submitted applications will not be rejected or held up due to incompleteness.</p>
